  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "To determine if someone has deleted you on LINE, you can look for certain indicators, although LINE does not explicitly notify you when someone removes you as a friend. Here are some ways to check:\n\n### 1. **Check Your Friends List**\n   - Open LINE and go to your **Friends** list.\n   - Search for the person in question.\n   - If you can\u2019t find them, they may have deleted you or blocked you.\n\n### 2. **Search for Their Profile**\n   - Use the **Search** feature in LINE and type their name or LINE ID.\n   - If their profile doesn\u2019t appear, they may have deleted you or changed their privacy settings.\n\n### 3. **Try Sending a Message**\n   - Send a message to the person.\n   - If the message doesn\u2019t go through or you see an error, it could indicate that they\u2019ve deleted you.\n\n### 4. **Check a Previous Chat**\n   - Open a previous chat with the person.\n   - If you see a message like **\u201cYou can no longer use this chat\u201d**, it means they have either deleted you or blocked you.\n\n### 5. **Check Your Timeline or Posts**\n   - If you\u2019ve interacted with their posts or timeline before, try finding their profile again.\n   - If you can\u2019t see their posts or profile, they may have removed you.\n\n### 6. **Ask a Mutual Friend**\n   - If you have a mutual friend, ask them to check if they can still see the person\u2019s profile or posts.\n\n### 7. **Create a New Group Chat**\n   - Try adding the person to a new group chat.\n   - If you can\u2019t add them, it may mean they\u2019ve deleted or blocked you.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- If someone blocks you on LINE, the indicators are similar to being deleted, so it can be hard to distinguish between the two.\n- LINE prioritizes user privacy, so there\u2019s no direct way to know for certain if someone has removed you.\n\nIf you suspect someone has deleted you, it\u2019s best to respect their decision and avoid further attempts to contact them unless necessary.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
